#week-title("Four", "Review, Commencement & The Letter to Self")

=== Core Teaching

The first year of study ends not with a conclusion, but with a moment of
honest review. What has been understood? What has remained opaque? What in the
inner work has shifted?

The Work does not "finish." The Plant Stone continues its digestion, and you
carry your experiences forward into the *Initiate tier*. This week is about
honouring the year's efforts and preparing for the secrets of water.

=== Topics This Week

- Honest review of Year One progress
- Preparation for Year Two: The Water Work
- Introduction to the नौ (nine) year personal cycle

#inner-work[
  *Letter to Your Future Self*

  Write a letter to yourself at the threshold of Year Two.
  - What did you set out to do in Month 1?
  - What actually happened?
  - What surprised you most?
  - What is your intention for the next year?

  Seal it. Do not open it until the end of Year Two.

  *Personal Year Calculation:*
  Add the month and day of your birth to the current calendar year and reduce to
  a single digit. Record this number and its alchemical resonance in your
  journal.
]

